content.detailedDescription: In the seconds of waking up with my eyes closed i saw two of what i've read about called (reptilian's)telling me i was not needed anymore with one of them giving an evil laugh like ha ha ha. i don't think this was a dream because they were so vivid. let me start at the beginning. about 5 years ago i would sometimes see out of the corner of my eye a bright green light streaming down thru my bedroom when i was just about ready to go to sleep. i would fall asleep with nothing more happening but wondering if something had. this would happen at least once a month. one night about 3;00 am i woke up to the sound of a low flying airplane coming right over the house and waited for a crash which never happened. there was a small private runway for small aircraft close to my house and i knew a pilot that flew there. he told me there was no reason for a plane to be that low, flying at that time of night. this sound was of a four engine prop plane that was full speed above the house. my wife and i travel in a rv and went to washington state where the green lights continued. i did see what i thought were three ufos that reminded me of helicopters without blades that i reported to mufon, but no encounters. we traveled south to arizona and about the second night there is when i saw the entity's, also with the green lights the night before. my wife thinks i'm nuts which may be the case. these entity's seemed like they were next to my bed talking to me. they were a dark green with lighter green highlites, the almond shaped black eyes with a snake like appearance and small pointed teeth. i can't remember ever being abducted or being on a space ship or anything like that and hope i don't but i fear that has been happening over the years, i just don't remember. my wife may be right, maybe i'm a loon.
content.summary: Reptilian laughing and telling me i was not needed anymore.

content.detailedDescription:
Miren, este objeto lo tuve a una distancia de aproximadamente 15 metros, media como unos diez o doce de diámetro; por las ventanas me observaron las siluetas que estaban ahí (ventanas tipo avión) era el disco de una sola pieza, no tenia luces, solo las emitidas por la parte inferior donde giraba y las de las ventanas, pasó calculo como a 5 o 10 kmts/hora donde yo estaba. quiero decir que lo ví desde muy lejos en dirección oeste-este (solo las luces), por lo que pensé en un avión, pero de repente realizó un giro y se dirigió hacia donde estaba yo (hacia el sur), pasó cerca de mí a una altura no mayor de 10 mts.Y se inclinó hacia mí (que fue cuando vi las sombras en las ventanas), no hacia ruido, no hubo apagón de luz, no emitia humo, pasó y se dirigió al estadio azteca (que se veía desde mi posición), se detuvo enmedio de él, emitió un rayo de luz blanco (ahora lo veo como un laser) que salía por la parte de abajo del ovni, le dió la vuelta alumbrandolo y al llegar nuevamente al centro del estadio que estaba vacio, lo apagó y en cuestión de 1 o 2 segundos máximos, aceleró y se perdió de vista hacia el este de la ciudad.
quiero pedirles me ayuden a comprender este avistamiento, ya que hasta el dia de hoy me sigo preguntando porqué si el ovni iba en una dirección totalmente diferente de donde me encontraba, giró y pasó cerca de mí de una manera tan lenta, que mas hubo, no lo recuerdo, ya que me han tratado de hipnotizar y la verdad me dicen que me agarro gritando pero no digo nada, si tienen manera de ayudarme a comprender esto, se los agradecería porque a pesar de haber pasado tantos años, sigo con lo inquietud de que cosas pasaron que no recuerdo yo. hago mención tamibien que me encontraba solo en el lugar, por lo cual no tengo ninguna prueba de ello.
gracias y es todo mi comentario.
content.summary: Discoidal que giraba en la parte infrerior, emitiendo luz anaranjada y azul por las ventanas donde se veian siluetas como humanas

content.detailedDescription:
On sunday, 3/6/2016 at approximately 8pm pst, i was at crssd music festival at the waterfront park in downtown san diego. this venue is next to the airport and across the bay from the coronado naval base. 
i noticed the object because i was facing west and saw a bright red cloud explosion in the sky. it caught my attention because it seemingly was happening out of nowhere as the rest of the sky was dark in that area. i almost thought it was a firework but i saw a red cloud that got bigger and something seemed like it ejected from the cloud, which changed directions leaving a trail of yellow/green/white light and fell straight down into the horizon/ocean. the entire event probably lasted around 10 seconds. 
at first i thought it was a ufo but than i realized that the event took place right above coronado naval base. i thought it could be a possible missile launch test. however after watching the videos of the mysterious lights spotted above los angeles, in early november 2015, which supposedly was a "missile launch test" - i am now unsure. the lights that i saw last night were much different in color, flight path and the time of the event was much shorter. perhaps this was a different type of missile? 
the event ended because i lost sight of the object because it seemingly fell straight down and most likely landed in the water.
content.summary: Red cloud explosion that ejected something out which then changed directions. it left a trail of yellow/green/white light and fell straight down

content.detailedDescription: I was standing out in front of the apartments. i was just looking up into the sky. i looked up and it appeared venus and mars were close together in the sky. the two objects were stationary and did not flicker like a star would as viewed through the atmosphere. i was just standing there looking up into the sky and enjoying the nice breeze. a neighbor was sitting in a chair by his apartment and said hello to me. i looked over and said hello and asked how he was doing. i looked back like 35-45 secs later at the sky and both objects had disappeared. i scanned the sky and they were no where to be seen and it was a clear night with no clouds and the area they were in was in the middle of the sky with nothing near them. i continued to look but they were not there anymore.
content.summary: Appeared to be venus and maybe mars

content.detailedDescription: Back in 1974 i was on my way home from work around 6:20 a.M. i was driving from laguna hills to my home and i was about 5 miles from my offramp to highway 39, beach blvd. when all of a sudden there was bright light and my car died. i coasted to the right side of the road. i don`t what happened next because i blacked out. the next thing i remembered was i was a whole 7 miles beyond highway 39 exit facing the opposite way. my car started with no problem. when i got back home i found out i that had lost a little over 30 minutes of time. all i can say is that for some reason i have had a picture in my mind of a motor that needs no fossil fuels. to this very day, there isn`t a day goes by than i still remember this motor for some reason. i am now 69 years old now and i feel the needed to get this off my chest.
content.summary: Bright lites an memory and time lost

content.detailedDescription: I was standing outside my apartment talking with the neighbor. we looked up at the sky around 23:45 and noticed it coming from the southwest. it first looked reddish and then became orange. at first i thought it could be the shuttle or space station. the object appeared spherical and it moved from southwest to the northeast. when it was approximately 45 degrees from what we thought was a star, the star shot east and south away from the larger orange sphere. the larger orange sphere continued moving to the northeast until it disappeared  over the horizon. the second object stayed in the sky pulsing different colors and sometime a dimmer sphere would appear next to it and then disappear. i was amazed to witness this encounter. the next couple of nights it was raining and cloudy so we could not view the sky. then both my neighbor and myself were outside the next couple of nights when the sky was clear at same time and did not see the objects again.
content.summary: Watched it come across sky. second smaller light shot away to the east abd south when it was getting closer.

content.detailedDescription: My family and i were traveling north bound on state highway 249 looking for a place to stop and eat when we saw the event take place. we noticed that there was a car dealership in the distance about 1/2 mile up the road with a giant spot light revolving on the roof of the establishment. while exiting the interstate we noticed that the spot light had come across something in the sky and at that very moment the object lit up as if it was on fire and descended straight down at a blistering speed. at first i thought it was a shooting star or fireworks but realized it couldn't be so due to the shear size, and trajectory of the object. i wasn't really scared the moment i recognized it but i was very intrigued, and sort of in shock. the object must have traveled 1000 within 2-3 seconds.. which is ridiculously fast in my book. the object disappeared about 100 ft above the ground never to be seen again that night.
content.summary: Object descended 1000 + ft. straight down very quickly within 3 seconds. object had a blue-ish green glow while coming down.

content.detailedDescription: Was headed to deer stand at about 515am on nov 10 2014. and was just looking at the stars. was a very clear nite. i noticed a triangle shaped group of three stars. they formed to me a perfect triangle. like a pyamid facing me.But a long way off. one star not as bright as other two. also not envolved in shooting.As i was looking ,all of a sudden the top star shot a pulsating light at the left bottom star. it lasted only about 3 seconds. i watched for a while after to see if it would do it again.But it didnt. would look back as i went on to deer stand . but nothing. note: see shooting stars quite often. but this was no shooting star.This was something aimed at a particular object and shot at it and no where else.Did not go beyond the object shot at.
content.summary: Was looking at stars and saw a 3 star group and then on1side 1 star began shooting a pusating light at the lowest star. approx 3 sec then nothin more.

content.detailedDescription: I was driving northbound on i-75.  i passed exit 217 and rounded a curve approaching the next exit 220.  as soon as i rounded the curve i noticed 4 or 5 lights in an arc formation in the sky north of me.  these looked like stars, but they were not.  i've never seen a constellation like this and they were lower than stars.  they vaguely reminded me of thiose "flares" famously observed in california years back. i also saw a couple of planes at different altitudes, which is not at all unusual.  the arc of lights hovered in the same formation while i drove and watched.  i wanted to exit on the 220b ramp, but i also wanted to continue watching.  i chose to continue driving and just watch a couple of minutes longer and exit at the ellenton exit and turn around there.  i was excited and puzzled and a little apprehensive about witnessing this. i could only see them when i was on the overpasses, as the road dipped down to groud level i lost sight of them because they would dip below the tree line.  the best view i had of them was while i drove over the manatee river bridge.  the first few moments i noticed them, i thought they might have been fluctuating from brightness to darker, but i cannot be sure because i was trying to focus on them and there were streetlights obstructing my view of them.  for the moments i could see them, they seemed pretty still.  when i turned around and started driving south bound on the interstate, i tried to catch glimpses of them in my rierview.  they were still there.  i exited at 220 and went to my destination to meet someone who i begged to go back with me for a quick drive to see if the lights were still there, and then he could see them too.  it probably took 10 minutes to get in the car and drive back to where i could see them, but they were gone.  i was amazed and disappointed that i missed witnessing them leave.
content.summary: Arc formation of 4 or 5 lights like stars all the same brightness seen from overpass on interstate 75

content.detailedDescription: We were watching the skies towards the south in ahwatukee. aircraft frequently depart and are readily identifiable. at approximately 7:30pm, in dark skies a small white flash occurred at about 80 degrees elevation in the western sky over the estrella mountains. the flash diminished to a low orange glowing object that appeared triangular. the color appeared to further diminish to black as it proceeded silently and rapidly in a straight line exiting to the east. i could not determine altitude but the orange surface approximated an aspirin. the surface was not a solid dull orange but had lines of glowing orange on a black surface.
content.summary: Small white flash in west then dark orange object losing color to black going east. no faa lights that are usually very apparent.

content.detailedDescription:
Hello, on february 21, 2016 at around 5:50 pm i witnessed 3 ufo's hovering outside. the sighting happen in hamilton, ontario, canada it was a very cloudy day, and the sun was setting at the west. i was in my bedroom about to turn on my playstation 4 that is located along my bedroom wall next to a large modern window with the blinds pulled up, as i turned on my ps4 i looked outside to see 3 bright objects in the sky hovering beside each other in a strange formation. at first i thought i was looking at airplanes/helicopters with their headlights turned on but their was no movement, after a few seconds maybe 6-9 seconds one ufo at the very top started blinking randomly, few seconds later the middle ufo dissapered and reappeared in the same exact spot it was in, i called my mom over who was in the kitchen to show her and she did not know what it could be... after a few more seconds 2 ufo's started blinking but very slowly and stopped, the 3rd ufo is slightly hard to see in the video the 3rd ufo is almost like transparent slightly visible, so i pulled out my ipad air 2 and started recording. 3 seconds into the recording and the ufo's started disappearing one by one. after the ufo's disappeared into the clouds (which is what it looked like) i looked into the sky all around me inside my bedroom window to notice anything unusual and everything looked normal like always. i went back to review the video and noticed a 4th ufo along the right side above the tall middle tree, that 4th ufo must have appeared and disappeared at the same time the last ufo on the left side disappeared. i did not see the 4th ufo when i was recording the other 3 ufo's on the left side disappear on my ipad screen. i have no idea how high and how far away the ufo's were, possibly hovering 2-5k feet high... the ufo's looked very large. i did not hear any strange noises or any aircraft engines, cars were driving on the road so perhaps that is why. the color of the ufo's was a yellow/orange almost like car lights. i have footage of the event and i uploaded it on youtube, one person has said it was a drone but that is the most idiotic comment i have heard. if you would like to view the video look up : ufo disappears into clouds - ontario, canada - on youtube. 

i included the video this time....
content.summary: Ufo disappears into clouds - ontario, canada
